    },
    "category": "csaf_security_advisory",
    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for dotnet6.0.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": ".NET is a managed-software framework. It implements a subset of the .NET framework APIs and several new APIs, and it includes a CLR implementation.\n\nNew versions of .NET that address a security vulnerability are now available. The updated versions are .NET SDK 6.0.126 and .NET Runtime 6.0.26.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* dotnet: Information Disclosure: MD.SqlClient(MDS) & System.data.SQLClient (SDS) (CVE-2024-0056)\n\n* dotnet: X509 Certificates - Validation Bypass across Azure (CVE-2024-0057)\n\n* dotnet: .NET Denial of Service Vulnerability (CVE-2024-21319)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
